\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 rude, scraggly }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 man walking in front of Mandri, }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 the}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  man }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 carrying}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91unconscious\u8217\'92 Mazyd Obo, his name was Seb. The man walking behind Mandri, the short and stout man who carried the torch, his name was Hill, and according to Hill, these were the only two things that Mandri needed to know. Don\u8217\'92t bother with \u8216\'91why\u8217\'92, or \u8216\'91what is going on\u8217\'92, or \u8216\'91I can\u8217\'92t see where I\u8217\'92m going\u8217\'92, no, the only thing that mattered was that Seb was in front and Hill was behind and that was the way things were going to be. If Mandri did so much as breathe too loud for Hill\u8217\'92s comfort, well}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ,}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  that was sufficient cause for an open handed smack on the back of the head, and it was impossible to not }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 make too much noise}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  because sound carried well in that pitch-black tunnel}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , a}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 nd Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s once-dead-legs were as stiff as rods so every step begged a groan. Every }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 bend of knee felt like a trigger exploding his thigh.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  Instead of striding through the dark like Hill wanted him to, Mandri shuffled through it on sensitive feet, doing what he could to avoid the trash that littered the floor, and that was hard to do too because the tunnel was a dumping ground. There was a horde of trash piled all the way up the low ceiling}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . It was}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  not a place for unshod feet. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The torchlight shadows of the p}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 icked-clean bones of small animals, splintered balkanut shells the size of skulls, curved clay shards of shattered jars, and all manner of organic waste, the worst of which were the cold and gooey lumps of muck that glistened when they welled up in between Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s toes\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Mandri }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t figure}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  w}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 hat this substance was}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  until Hill stepped in it, too.}
