\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Seb rolled his eyes, turned a cold shoulder to Hill\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s indignation, and started off again into the dark. Hill nudged Mandri to follow.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Seb }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 said, }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t play no blame games with me. W}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ho\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s the one }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 pilin\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92 up}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  all this trash up in here, huh? Ya know there\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s a pit for all this, too, but ya}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ll}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  too lazy}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  Get yourself together fore you come and pick on my habits.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Seb wrapped up his }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 complaint with a snort before it blossomed into a }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 harangue}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He had to}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  readjusting Obo\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s dead weight }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 to accommodate it}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mandri followed along, eyes searching the ground for a clean edge of stone to scrape his shit-stained foot against. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This tunnel was the most loathsome place that }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 he}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  had ever seen}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Black moldy growths pickled the ceiling}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , cramped}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  tight with trash,}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  not one thing in it was whole, yet with each step Mandri was becoming more and more certain that this wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t truly Shis. This was life in all it\u8217\'92s lived-in-ness, and Mandri could think of no surer a sign of plenty than a deep trash heap. But maybe every nation\u8217\'92s trash found its way down to Shis as a kind of punishment that the dead must bear for not cleaning up after themselves. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 It wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t until the trio left this rubbish tunnel and spilled out into a }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 cleaner, }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 roomier tunnel that Mandri was sure\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 this was }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 a}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  regular old }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 cave system,}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 not some corridor of Shis. It was d}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ark and foreboding,}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  yes,}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  but the objects that lay strewn around the }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 brown}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  rock floor were too banal to be }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 instruments of some grand design}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 On o}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ne side }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 of this tunnel }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 was a store of chopped lumber, and stacked cross-wise on the other were plump }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 canvas }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 bags}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  branded with a black Hrkan compass rose. Strewn on the floor in between this stolen grain and the firewood was all manner of idle obstructions\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 beer pots, holey-soled and stringless leather boots, a bundle of arrows propped up inside a beer pot, more beer pots.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Th}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 is dark passage emptied out into a}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  yet}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  bigger one, where the ceiling was twice Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s height. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Seb picked his way around all this junk as if he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d placed each piece himself, like a pampered toddler waddling through scattered toys. The pain in Mandri\u8217\'92s legs flared up as he struggled to keep pace.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He stubbed his toe on a, and it was in that moment that he accepted the fact that}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  truly had been brought back to life.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 It remained to be seen if this was positive development.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 At the very least it was an interesting development.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Interesting}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  that he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d been raised from the dead}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . Perhaps more interesting was}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  that these ratty bandits had somehow captured a Mazyd. The Mazydai were beings of storied power, cornerstones of Hrkan Lordship, yet there was Mazyd Obo, }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 his pale form }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 limp and shoulder-slung like a freshly slaughtered sty-pig}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , his bald head bobbing with Seb\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s every step}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . It was hard to believe anyone could bring a Mazyd down so low, and that these two ratty bandits were involved was inconceivable. Seb was as unimposing as an outland man could be, dirty and hungry looking, with sunken eyes. He looked like desperation more than a man, }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 not the dangerous desperation, the sad kind of}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  desperation }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 that he}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  could defeat by simply looking away.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mandri snuck a look behind at Hill. Hill had his plump pinky finger stuck halfway up his own nose, digging for gold.}
