\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mandri }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 stood up and he started to move in the direction he supposed Seb wanted him to go. He figured his way was true because Seb\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s knife didn\u8217\'92t correct him. The two of them walked like this, bumbling through the pitched-black dark, toes and knees crashing into whatever happened to be in their way, clank of fired clay and the . Eventually they came to yet another tunnel, one which gave way}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , some fifty meters away,}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  t}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 o the blinding light of day.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 One quick glance at this spot of sunlight was enough to imprint a white circle into Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s vision}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  that stayed true wherever he looked}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  It was so  that was effectively blind when they stumbled out of the cave. He only knew he was outside because of the }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 warmth}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  of sunlight that}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  wash}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ed}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  over }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 his }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 skin. Seb let go of his arm, and Mandri}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s aching legs}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 took this as a to collapse. He sank}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  to his knees, }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 and instead of meeting rock his skin met warm, soothing sand}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . He dug his hands into it. It was so damn comfortable. He wanted to }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 wriggle into it like a sand flea}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Where is Ayram!?\u8221\'94 Seb shouted.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Ayram\u8217\'92s not here.\u8221\'94 }
